  "text": "where B is the Bulk modulus. In deriving Eqs. (1) and (2) it was assumed that the material is virtually incompressible in terms of volume, that the cross-section of the block, normal to the direction of the applied load, remains plane and horizontal and also that the free vertical surfaces take up parabolic forms. Horton et al. [CITATION_1] eliminated the assumption of a parabolic profile and derived a different expression:",
